<TITLE> US Defense Sec. Gates fractures shoulder after ice slip </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Washington, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US Defense Secretary Robert Gates fractured his right shoulder on Tuesday evening after slipping on ice, the Pentagon said on Wednesday. He received medical care and is continuing to fulfill duties of his job, said Pentagon spokesman Bryan Whitman. But Gates will not appear at a congressional hearing on the US defense budget scheduled for Wednesday morning. The Washington DC area has been hit by icy weather over the last two days.
